b'' b'' b"i've been able to configure xterm so that i can type in accented characters." b"i'm using x11r5, with iso8859 fonts, my shell is tcsh with the following" b'definitions b'setenv lc_ctype iso_8859_1' b'stty pass8' b'' b'then, i add the following in my .xdefaults file:' b'' b'xterm*eightbitinput: true' b'xterm*eightbitoutput: true' b'' b'xterm*vt100.translations: #override b"meta<key': keymap(aigu) \\n\\" b'meta<key`: keymap(grave) \\n\\' b'meta<key^: keymap(circ) \\n\\' b'meta<key\\\\,: keymap(ced)' b'xterm*vt100.aigukeymap.translations: b'~shift <keye: string(0xe9) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keye: string(0xc9) keymap(none) \\n\\' b'~shift <keyc: string(0xe7) \\n\\' b'<key c: string(0xc7)' b'xterm*vt100.gravekeymap.translations: b'~shift <keye: string(0xe8) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keye: string(0xc8) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'~shift <keyu: string(0xf9) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keyu: string(0xd9) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'~shift <keya: string(0xe0) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keya: string(0xc0) keymap(none)' b'xterm*vt100.circkeymap.translations: b'~shift <keye: string(0xea) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keye: string(0xca) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'~shift <keyu: string(0xfb) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keyu: string(0xdb) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'~shift <keyi: string(0xee) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keyi: string(0xce) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'~shift <keyo: string(0xf4) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<keyo: string(0xd4) keymap(none)' b'xterm*vt100.cedkeymap.translations: b'~shift <keyc: string(0xe7) keymap(none)\\n\\' b'<key c: string(0xc7) keymap(none)' b'' b"this makes the meta-{',`,^} keys behave as dead keys." b'' b'of course, this only works for xterm. for emacs, my solution is to install the' b'lucid version of gnuemacs and to load the x-compose library.' b'' b'' b'hope this helps,' b'' b'' b'eric' b'--' b'inria rocquencourt, projet rodin "les bons gongs font' b'bp le chesnay cedex les bonzes amis"' b'tel (gotlib)' 